&gt; Hi all,
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m in the process of writing a JSP application and I would like to
&gt; run unit tests on the server as well as locally.  The motivation for
&gt; this is that invariably, you end up running different JVM versions (or
&gt; architectures at least) on the server and locally, which can introduce
&gt; really annoying bugs.
&gt; 
&gt; I was thinking of making a custom taglib for running the tests.  It
&gt; would be used similarly to the following:
&gt; 
&gt; &lt;mylib:test-output&gt;
&gt;   &lt;mylib:test-case testClass=&quot;mypackage.tests.UserTest&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;mylib:test-case testClass=&quot;mypackage.tests.DbConnectTest&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;mylib:test-case testClass=&quot;mypackage.tests.UtilsTest&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;mylib:test-suite testClass=&quot;mypackage.tests.SomeTests&quot; /&gt;
&gt; &lt;/mylib:test-output&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; This would then print out an HTML table summarizing the results of the
&gt; unit tests and their success or failure.
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;ve looked around for existing software to suite this functionality,
&gt; but haven&#39;t found an exact match.  I looked at Cactus
&gt; (http://jakarta.apache.org/cactus/), HttpUnit
&gt; (http://httpunit.sourceforge.net/) and TagUnit
&gt; (http://www.tagunit.org/).  Have I missed something?
&gt; 
&gt; I would appreciate any input.
&gt; 
&gt; --Peter
